<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880715-0059 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Raytheon Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RTN </CO><IN> ERN </IN><TEXT>   Raytheon Co., Lexington, Mass., said second-quarter net income rose 10% to $122.3 million from $110.8 a year earlier. Per-share earnings jumped 23% on a 6.5% rise in sales.    Improved operating performance and a lower effective tax rate-31.1%, compared with the year-earlier 34.9% -- contributed to the earnings increase for the quarter, ended July 3, the electronics and aircraft company said. Completion of a 20 million-share buy-back program helped push pershare earnings to $1.84 from the year-earlier $1.50.    Sales rose to $2.04 billion from $1.92 billion for the quarter ended June 28, 1987. Backlog increased to $8.76 billion from $8.26 billion.    &quot;As we reported in the first quarter, Beech (Aircraft) and energy services have turned around,&quot; said Thomas L. Phillips, chairman. &quot;As a result, all five business segments were again profitable in the second quarter.&quot;    First-half net rose 11%, per-share net climbed 23% and sales rose 8.7%. </TEXT></DOC>